### 2. Database Schema & Migrations

#### [NEW] [schema.js](file:///C:/Users/rephr/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/oratio-dental/src/lib/server/db/schema.js)

**18 tables** (★ = new/changed from v1):

| Table | Key Details |
|-------|------------|
| `users` | UUID, name, username, password_hash, role, doctor_code, is_active |
| ★ `doctor_shifts` | **NEW** — doctor_id FK, day_of_week (0–6), start_time, end_time |
| `patients` | id (O000001 format), NIK unique, all demographics, document_id FK |
| `patient_disease_history` | personal/family, FK to terminology_master |
| `patient_allergy` | substance_code + reaction_code FKs |
| `patient_medication` | code FK, dosage, note |
| `terminology_master` | system (SNOMED/ICD-10/ICD-9-CM/KFA), code, display |
| `documents` | polymorphic patient_id / encounter_id, file metadata |
| `encounters` | id=YYYYMM{DoctorCode}NNNNNN, form_mode, SOAP, status |
| `status_history` | Arrived/In Progress/Finished, start/end timestamps |
| `encounter_odontograms` | dentition, occlusi, torus, palatum, diastema, anomali |
| `odontogram_details` | tooth_number, surface, keadaan, restorasi, ICD refs |
| `encounter_prescriptions` | KFA code, product, dosage, quantity |
| `encounter_referrals` | doctor_code, date, note |
| `encounter_diagnoses` | FK to terminology_master (ICD-10) |
| `encounter_procedures` | FK to terminology_master (ICD-9-CM), tooth, surface |
| `items` | Master items, user_id (doctor), price |
| `encounter_items` | quantity, price_at_time, computed subtotal |
| `payments` | mode, discount, totals, payment_type, ★ **no reference_number**, card_number (conditional) |

#### ★ NEW: `doctor_shifts` Table

```sql
CREATE TABLE doctor_shifts (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    doctor_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    day_of_week INT NOT NULL CHECK (day_of_week BETWEEN 0 AND 6),
        -- 0=Sunday, 1=Monday, ..., 6=Saturday
    start_time TIME NOT NULL,
    end_time TIME NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
    CHECK (end_time > start_time),
    UNIQUE (doctor_id, day_of_week, start_time)
);
```

**Example data**: Doctor A (BS) works Sunday 10:00–17:00, Tuesday 13:00–15:00, Friday 08:00–10:00. This table is managed by Admin and displayed in Kasir's appointment form so kasir can see which doctors are available on a given day.

#### ★ Updated: `payments` Table Changes

- **Removed**: `reference_number` column
- **`card_number`**: only populated when patient pays with card-based payment types (EDC-*)
- **Added**: `cashier_id` already exists — will show cashier name prominently in the payment UI

#### [NEW] [seed.js](file:///C:/Users/rephr/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/oratio-dental/drizzle/seed.js)

Seeds: default admin, 14 doctors as users, allergy reaction codes (30 items), sample doctor shifts.

